stylometry: There are advantages to using simulation models.  One of the advantages is being able to complete what if analysis for businesses.  Simulation Models allow you to perform real life situations and see the different answers you receive based on different variables.   In many situations simulation models are the only physical example a company can perform in deciding what works best for their situation.  This can allow a company to save alot of money depending on whether or not the answer it gave them was correct.  Businesses would use a simulation problem to decide how many different cash registers to use at a clothing apparel store.  THey would be able to use the simulation and take into consideration customer waiting time in line.  You could use a simulation model in order to determine how many shoes to order based on different variables such as estimated demand and time of the year.  Simulation models allow businesses to work out problems or situaitons they will experience in their jobs.
